\begin_layout Plain Layout
Will this become my magnum opus? Do I feel like it ? I had the idea, I wanted
 to toy with.
 Make it into something with a didactic quality.
 Will it sound sacrilegious? The work of a conceited person? I cannot know,
 nor should I care.
 I saw a dream today.
 It kind of reminded me of that idea.
 The idea being, what has stopped the evolution of man? What is the one
 thing that holds man back, as a race, as a society, as the Children of
 God?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
It is evil, in all its forms.
 It seeps into the soul of each person in a myriad ways.
 It has tormented the world we live in.
 This is what churches do.
 They try to appease to the better nature of man.
 They try to turn him away from evil, see a clear path towards redemption.
 Spiritual redemption, a rebirth of mind and soul that should lead to the
 utopia we have always seeked, and always complained that is too far away.
 Maybe it's not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In this novel I will attempt to portray what it could be like to shed money
 and value as a system, not in the anarchist (or God forbid, communist)
 sense, but in the sense taught by Jesus Christ; love those close to you
 like yourself.
 The 2nd coming of the Christ could be this indeed; a hominum opus, a work
 of man, the most important work man ever attempted.
 It might have been designed by God himself, but as is the usual question,
 if God loves us all and wishes the best for us, why doesn't he yanks us
 back into heaven so we can all be happy and just forget the whole thing?
 Because the fall from grace was our choice, and getting back in should
 be ours as well.
 We are a free race of beings, a community of free and independent souls.
 What we must realise is that salvation, evolution, the beginning of a transhuma
n era, a new perfect loving society happy and healthy beings is within our
 grasp, and our power.
 It is indeed, our prerogative, what we should be actively looking to create.
 We have the guide, the doors are open and waiting.
 We need to take the first steps, which we have failed to do with repetitive
 accuracy for two millenia.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Is this more of a manifesto or a creed instead of a novel? I don't wish
 to make it overtly so.
 I do wish people to learn from it though, or at least get their heads (and
 their hearts), feeling I might be right.
 Is it too grandiose? Probably.
 Do I really know what I'm doing, what I believe in, or what exactly I want
 to write? No, of course not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
But I know that the evil that men do, is the money, the riches, the power
 exerted over each other.
 It is the lack of sharing, as was the mantle of Christ, that is which creates
 dissent, which creates problems, friction, competition.
 Is it in the nature of man as an animal to be like that? To mark his territory,
 provide for his young ones and maintain his existence by killing off the
 others around him.
 Is there need any more to kill for food? Or have we as a species developed
 past that point and now instead kill for money, women or blow? Do we kill
 to preserve a status quo?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
It's fear that drives societies to accept the goings-on in this world with
 such lamentable ease.
 Fear of losing one's job, or teeth.
 Fear of the future 'me', the future us.
 There's a saying 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

fear is what safeguards the poor ones
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 It refers to sheep.
 We are poor, lost sheep, adrift in an ocean of uncertainty that keeps us
 in check.
 We cannot yet shed our inhibitions and instincts of self-preservation,
 yet we must if we are to evolve, and evolution can only come towards the
 path God has pre-ordained.
 In itself, it's leap of faith that mankind must take before it obliterates
 itself or stagnates to death.
 I like to think of it as what the God-Emperor of Mankind in WH40K or the
 God-Emperor Leto II had to undertake: guiding humanity through the stars.
 Yet, I shall start with simpler and less lofty goals.
 Abolish money, and usher in a christian society based on a singularity
 effect that we are so close to achieving.
 It's the Star Trek philosophy: what if there was no need for money and/or
 resources were practically limitless: Would there still be the same problems?
 I want to see it the other way: What if resources could be spread good
 enough for everyone to enjoy the basic, good things in life? Would we need
 money then?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In any case, money I believe, and its pursuit and glorification, with all
 the power that comes with it (which is probably a far superior reason than
 money itself - who needs all those billions? But the power that they endow
 the owner with - the power to regulate the lives of thousands, the power
 to have practically anything at a whim..
 That is the danger - man mistaking himself for something other than flesh
 and man, borne of woman).
 That might be my belief, but I shall try to systematically make it the
 only viable logical option, not by point of a theological explanation or
 approval, but by much more mundane human scales, beliefs, and measures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Anyway I think I get the idea - but how to pass it on? With a little bit
 of adventure, drama, thrills and frills, perhaps humor as well?
\end_layout

